  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And then there was a overflow of crowd from the main temple that could not afford to buy seats.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "There was an extra hall for those people as well, like an auditorium that we call here.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "To characterize it as which one was conservative and which one was reformed, it's very difficult.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Because conservative here means something different than conservative 50 or 60 or 70 years ago.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "In those days, there was no such thing as reformed.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "You were either conservative or hasidic or ultra hassidic.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was, there were only the organizations like Halutz, [?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Halutzim, ?] Zionist organizations, and there were labor organizations and obviously Communists as well.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But to say that there should have been some educational facilities beyond high-- beyond public school, Dobra was too small for that.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I would say that as long as Marshal Pilsudski was the president of Poland.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was the signatory to a special document, as a matter of fact, that was mandated by the United States at the League of Nations, when Poland became-- got independence, Poland became a state.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They had to sign a separate mandate, in which they have proclaimed to give equal rights to minorities in Poland.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so as long as Marshal Pilsudski was the president, there was a [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] polite [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] but not completely tolerable relationship between non-Jews and Jews.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Something was always in the way of their Roman Catholic scriptures and the Roman Catholic [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] fathers that have priests-- the priests that have preached in their churches that was not always allowed them to accept Jews.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They lived too long with the [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] out-aged and outlived [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] kind of enigma that existed against Jews.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
